The paper discusses the topic of explainability in Artificial Intelligence, which is a common theme in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also focuses on the use of ontologies to improve the understandability of global post-hoc explanations, which relates to the sub-categories of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper presents a user study that measures the effectiveness of the proposed approach, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
